The paper proposes a method for investigating the transferability of knowledge learned from pre-trained deep neural networks (PR-DNNs) and applies it to two important problems in transfer learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on computer vision tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves measuring the similarity of features extracted from PR-DNNs, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing attribution maps, which suggests that it may belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves investigating the transferability of knowledge between different tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
